You are given three inputs:
An integer representing a person's age.
A floating-point number representing their height in meters.
A string representing their name.
Input Format

The first line contains an integer age.
The second line contains a floating-point number height.
The third line contains a string name.
Constraints

1 <= age <= 120
0.5 <= height <= 2.5
1 <= length of name <= 100
name contains only alphabets without spaces.
Output Format

** Name is Age years old and Height meters tall.**

Sample Input 0

25  
1.75  
Pradeep
Sample Output 0

Pradeep is 25 years old and 1.75 meters tall.
Sample Input 1

18  
2.00  
Alice
Sample Output 1

Alice is 18 years old and 2.00 meters tall.

Code

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
       Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
       int age =sc.nextInt();
       float height =sc.nextFloat();
       sc.nextLine();
       String name =sc.nextLine();
       System.out.printf("%s is %d years old and %.2f meters tall.\n",name,age,height);
        sc.close();
        
    }
}
